      "description": "Offered is an investment-grade 1987 Porsche 911 Carrera, featuring the highly sought-after Getrag G50 transaxle with Borg-Warner synchronizers for precise, robust gear selection. The 3.2-liter air-cooled flat-six remains in factory-spec, exhibiting impeccable compression across all cylinders and a dry crankcase free of seepage. The Bosch Motronic DME fuel injection ensures a linear power curve, while the chassis retains its original torsion bar setup and Bilstein dampers, providing the tactile feedback synonymous with the Carrera's rear-engine architecture. This specimen boasts original Grand Prix White finish with consistent micrometer readings and flawless Fuchs forged wheels. A mechanically transparent example with zero deferred maintenance.",
